    for (int i = firstMethodEvaluation; i &lt;= lastMethodEvaluation; i++) {
        this.atualMethodEvaluation = i;
        returnBestKTree = methodEvaluation.get(i).bestK(i); // Get TreeMap from another method
        TreeMap&lt;String, TreeMap&lt;Integer, Double&gt;&gt; innerMap = new TreeMap&lt;&gt;();
        
        innerMap.put(&quot;k&quot;, returnBestKTree.get(&quot;k&quot;));
        innerMap.put(&quot;mediaMovelArr&quot;, returnBestKTree.get(&quot;mediaMovelArr&quot;));
        innerMap.put(&quot;angularCoefficientArr&quot;, returnBestKTree.get(&quot;angularCoefficientArr&quot;));

        allData.get(topicId).put(i, innerMap);
    }
}
```

I&#39;ve created a new `innerMap` for each iteration of the inner loop and added the required entries to it. 

Then, I&#39;ve used the unique `i` value as the key to store the `innerMap` in the outer `TreeMap` associated with the specific `topicId`. 

This way, **you won&#39;t overwrite the entries**, and you&#39;ll have a separate inner map for each `i` value within each `topicId`.

